        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 2:40PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 240 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Organ, moving southwest at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
White Sands Missile Range Main Post, Organ, Talavera, East Mesa,
Northeast Las Cruces, Dripping Springs, Aguirre Springs, Portions of
Organ Mountains Desert Peaks National Monument, Soledad Canyon, and
San Augustin Pass.

This includes Highway 70 in New Mexico between mile markers 156 and
178.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
